HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1489
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Michael Green of York
Institute on being named the 2026 BCAT Class
AA Coach of the Year in girls' basketball.
WHEREAS, this General Assembly takes great pleasure in recognizing those
Tennesseans who have distinguished themselves as great athletic coaches while motivating the
young men and women under their charge to reach for and attain the greatest heights; and
WHEREAS, Michael Green, girls' basketball coach at York Institute, has been named
the 2026 Basketball Coaches Association of Tennessee (BCAT) Class AA Coach of the Year,
an honor that not only recognizes a successful season, but also a sustained period of
excellence that has firmly established the Dragonettes as one of the top programs in the State
of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Coach Green led the Dragonettes to their fifth consecutive state tournament
appearance this season, an accomplishment that speaks to the program's consistency and
competitive edge under his watch; and
WHEREAS, Coach Green and the Dragonettes advanced to the state title game for the
second consecutive season, once again finishing as runner-up; and
WHEREAS, the team's back-to-back trips to the state championship game underscore
the resilience and confidence that Coach Green has instilled in his charges; and
WHEREAS, Coach Green and the Dragonettes also captured both the district and region
championships for the fourth consecutive season, further solidifying their position as a
powerhouse program; and
WHEREAS, Coach Green led the Dragonettes to an outstanding overall record of 30-7
this season by utilizing the hallmarks of his coaching philosophy, which includes a balanced mix
of offense and defense and strong team chemistry; and
HJR1489
018202
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Coach Green has built an exemplary culture, centered on accountability,
preparation, and player development, that has resulted in sustained success; and
WHEREAS, an outstanding teacher and mentor, he is adept at maximizing player
potential and fostering a team-first mentality among his players; and
WHEREAS, by emphasizing fundamentals and mental toughness, Coach Green has
built the Dragonettes into a team that competes consistently against some of the best teams in
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Michael Green is among the most respected coaches in high school
basketball, and he is most worthy of our approbation on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Michael Green of York Institute on being
named the 2026 Basketball Coaches Association of Tennessee (BCAT) Class AA Coach of the
Year in girls' basketball and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success on the
court and in life.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
